values: havent updated in forever but im happy..i have the best boyfriend, best roommate, have experienced unbelievable things, live in an awesome apartment, have a great job, love my major, love my family, love everything God is teaching me...GOD IS GREAT!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

I havent updated inforever...i really like my boyfriend =)  I thought it was bad cuz I thought i should be single...but I realized that he WAS PERFECT..and there was no reason for me to be UNHAPPY when they PERFECT boy was right infront of me!  I want to stay in FL for the summer but I do not like being away from my family for so long!!!! When u least think it wil happen..it will.  Well that is so true.  So I  will update later but ive been to DC, NY, And NH in a car with my friends at PBA for a week, we had a hurricane and took off..it was fun and i will update later...but I saw Josh while i was there and funny thing happened but...me and one of the guys I was with...fell for eachother...i have been on my WAITING FOR GOD and the pefect guy, and i feel like it hasnt been long enough, but we def act like we r dating, we said wed just be friends, but its hard, i guess its self control, but tomm we r going to the beach and praying together about it, but i just wanted to ask u all to pray for me, that i can accpet it if God wants us to wait and have self control and if he wants us to be together that I will know.  Neways I will update later..I love u all!

"The LORD your God does w you; he will never leave you nor forsake you."  Deuteronomy 31:6.  So um. Where to start.  I feel like my life is contanstly changing.  Not too be dramatic, but I have been thinking and I have had an incredible life, full of wonderful expierences.  A wonderful childhood, a wonderful teenager years, and now growing into an adult.  I was blessed with a wonderful family and friends my whole life.  I grew up living in an apartment buliding with best friends everywhere, but it saddens me to say once junior high hit those friendships faded.  But I gained the greatest friends a girl could ask for.  Alot of ppl lose touch after high school but I realized who out of those ppl are my true friends.  It is pretty sad that some of my best friends in junior high and high school dont even talk to me nemore, but the truth is, if I was still the girl I was back then, wed be friends, but since I have changed, we arent.  This past year was intense for me.  I had to step out my comfort zone.  I actually told my whole public speaking class this story.  I grew up as a cathloic girl, always going to church because I was told to.  I went to youth group because I had to.  I always kinda enjoyed it, but would NEVER admit it, I would just sit and complain with my friends about how bored I was.  I cheered for my church so it kept me involved.  I was a cathloic girl, not a christian.  So my mom left the cathloic church because she didnt agree with the man made laws nemore, but I wouldnt leave because I loved cheerin for the church.  I use to go to church to see boys on the basketball team.  My mom was saved while I was in high school, but I thought she was Obssessed with God.  She drove me crazy.  The more she talked to me the more I pushed her away.  The further I got from God.  I was into my friends, drinking, partying, guys, and not living a life with God.  I was like mom, I believe in God, I am a good person, I am going to heaven dont worry!  Funny huh? I wasnt even that nice of a person.  I had friends who were stuck up, and therefore I had the rep of being a snobby cheerleader, I would never stick up for peers when my friends were mean to them.  I would never stick up for anyone.  I realize now some of those "friends" werent friends.  So on mothers day my senior year I went to my moms church.  The play Heavens Gate, Hells Furry  was being performed.  That was the day I knew my life had to change.  Soon after that I visited FSC, and thought, "THIS IS IT"!!! I am going to grow spirituality.  So i left my life behind and went!  So I met an AMAZING christian girl, and we got close.  She took me to a ministry and held my hand as I cried and stood up with many others who were proclaiming they wanted a life with Jesus Christ.  So then after that I met a really nice guy.  He also helped me in my walk.  He told me that he could see there was more to me, and to just be myself.  He prayed for me.  So soon after that, things fell.  The girl had started dating someone and I barley saw her, and he stopped talking to me because of all the drama at the school.  SO where did I findmyself? Back in the game of drinking and guys.  So soon after that I started feeling sorry for myself.  So what happens next? I think I NEED A BOYFRIEND! So I start dating a "Christian".  Well...everything went down from there.  I put God on the back burner and this boyfriend became my life.  So once school was out I went home, none of my friends wanted to associate with me becuz I didnt drink nemore, WELL one DID! and the only reason was because she was a Christian =) But we didnt hangout that much, and I had a few friends but not many.  So basically my boyfriend and I broke up.  And i felt so alone.  I realized that I needed to put God first, and he was the only one who was going to fill that whole.  And that he gave me singleness as a gift, so I could spend my time growing and pleasing Him, and that the day I was ready hed give me my prince charming.  SO I deciated my summer to Jesus.  I fell in love with Him, got baptized by the HOly Spirit. WHOA.  =)  So then it was time to pick a school.  Was I gonan transfer? NOPE..I was going to stay at FSC becuz I realized I could find Christians newhere.  But WHAT?  A BEEEEAAUUUUTTTIFUL girl named ERIN started emailing me about PBA...and she was a blessing from above =)  Soooo I went to youth group and saw that someone had a PBA shirt!!!!!! So I was getting all this signs like WHOA.  SOOO I prayed about it like crazy.  And finally God told me, "Jamie GO TO PBA" I realized it was not about ME, and it was about HIM, I was scared of leaving my comfort zone, but I knew to glorify Him I had to obey.  So here I am..and I feel like I lost all my friends at home..and lately I dont feel like my friends at florida southern care either...and im kinda lonely here too.  Like I dont feel like ME...I use to be sooooo happy...soooo fun...sooo crazy and hyper...so active..now im always doin hw..maybe its part of growing up?  I uset o be so friendly and outgoing and now im MISS SHY...i hate it.  I guess I have to give it time.  But its like I get intimated by others sometimes.  I feel like they are better than me because they have been Christians for so long.  But then I realize we rnt suppose to do that, I am growing and I am in love with that =) I guess I am just ramboling, tomm is going to be great, ill go to church and be happy, I guess I am going to stop feeling sorry for myself because I am so blessed, who else has paretns drive them around the world? Haha! Well I know thins will turn around...cheerleading tryouts this week! whoop! I mite be goin on a mission trip...ohh the Lords blessing me..I have no reason to complain! I just have to organize my time better so I can have fun too =) Ok bye all! =)

Ok so ya..Im in one of those moods....So PBA is like awesome...exatly what I excepted...everyone is in Love with the Lord and its so amazing to see.  I really like it!  But I was having a rough time getting use to it..I was def comparing it to FSC, and always on the phone with ppl from FSC..when I realized I have to let go..its okay to be friends and keep in touch..but I should be bonding here....I realized so many ppl have made such great bonds and connections and I honestly havent.  Don't get me wrong everyone I met has been amazing.  But for some odd reason I have been sucha baby here.  I thought I was over this..But like I dont like to go to things by myself...and I am like scared to meet ppl.  Like lets start off with EX:1...boy calls A MILLION times tryin to meet up with me, but since im scared I always just ignore him...blew that..where he was an amazing child of God and could have been a great friend.  Then there were so many ppl who offered to take me out and I never took them up.  I never take invites newhere, and I dont act friendly....so I went to campus ministries and I prayed with someone there, I am thinking of joining the prayer team and another ministry, I think im going on a mission trip toooo! So ill meet ppl there...then theres cheerleading..a passion of mine..but they had like open stunting and I never went..and I thought of not doin it then i thought hey i kinda do..and i never went cuz i was scared..intimadted..why do i have such low self esstem and no confidence.  Im thinking everyone is better than me, everyone knows eachother, blah blah...o my gosh I should suck it up...and GOOO if God wants me to do it ill make it! if not its not meant to be..but whats the worse that can happen..i dont make it..really not that bad, btu for some reason im still so scared.  Its like im scared of all these new things, but i should be excited, and the sooner i do them the sooner ill be comfortable.  Then theres the point im always doin school work i never have time for nething, i need to work on time managment..if ne1 is reading this please pray for me..that i can figure out my time skills, and that i can have mroe courage and confidence, and that I can act the way God wants me to and be friednly so I can make better connections with ppl.  I hate how ppl can talk online and then its like so different in person..I mite just give up the internet...its so gay..thanks to my roomey im realizing this..I know God sent me here to step up..and I cant think hell do everything..I have to stop bein sucha baby...I need to go out have fun and relax..I need to join things, and not be scared to go places new.  Ok im gonna go study but I had to let this all out...

I am leaving at 530 am and our flight takes off at 7am.  I cant sleep.  Im too excited.  Tomm will b a long day thou.  Take off at 7 but have to stop over in baltimore and then to West palm...then to orlando to get my car and back to west palm.  So nervous about being out of my comfort zone but so excited cuz everyone seems so great.  I feel like its awesome, i have all my fsc friends just 3 hours away. I wish closer, but i guess its best they rnt, id never make friends if they were, cuz id always b wit them, which would defeat the purpose of leaving, haha.  Oh and too Nicole, I love you too, I just didnt put u in my entry becuz I was talkin to Jamie and Lauren for the past couple days and so I put them in the entry cuz they were on my mind.  Im goin to miss u also like crazy! But i know well keep in touch.  Well neways I pray I wont be anxious or shy.  I need sleep but i cant, I am about to step into a new enviornment where my life is gonna b changed...am i ready? I hope so ; )  Sometimes life moves so fast and we arent ready, but we have to be.  Who knows what this year holds, but im excited, if I cheer, get a job at the hotel, end of with a boyfriend, have amazing friends, go on missions, get into ministry, who knows, but i kno this year holds alot of amazing things.  I was thinking of how my life keeps changing and i just wish i could have one place where I was happy, but I realized God blessed me with PBA and an amazing upcomin year, he blessed me w amazing ppl at fsc, and amazing family, and even amazing friends at home.  So ready or not, PBA here I come =)
Goodnite!

I am leaving in two days!!!! o man...so excited...was nervous but now im just excited..welcome week sounds like a blast..shane and shane concert, time on the beach, competitions..meeting people..yes!  Soo I have a new roommate..shes from new mexico..im going to miss Lauren and Jamie sooo much! Ive been talkin to them alot lately.  But I know PBA is where I belong.  But neways..I have realized that I am so blessed.  I have the most amazing family ever.  I kind of dont want to leave them.  But I know I have to.  Its scary to think we grow up so fast.  I have the best relationship with them and I am so lucky.  But I know I have to have my own life.  I was so happy at FSC thinking I had it all, and now its like everything is brand new again...new friends...new life.  ohhh man...Im just so happy I am so blessed by the amazing family I have!

So then I get in my car and drive back to WPB.  So Ill be a lil north for a day.  If ne1 wants to see me for a day please call.  Cuz Ill b there kinda near Daytona if u dont kno where Flagler beach is ; ). Then I will be in WPB for like 2 days be4 I have to move in so if ur south give me a call =)  I wanna see ppl b4 school starts!  So then I move in the 23rd but welcome week starts the 4th.  I AM SO NERVOUS!  I am tryin not to.  I dont want to claim up and being unfriendly.  Do not be afraid, little flock, for your father has been pleased to give you the kingdom.  Luke 12:32.  I have always been shy before I met ppl thou.  I just hope I don't claim up.  I mean SO many people have been so kind to me ALREADY!  Ppl have offered to show me around, giving me their numbers, everything.  So maybe instead of being a shy baby I should take them up and be friendly!  I just feel like im bugging ppl cuz they have there group of friends already.  Soooo the roommate situation, I talk to her,  but she isnt coming back.  Residence life said dont worry they wont make me pay for  the whole suite, but theres a big waiting list and they will put sum1 else in..Kinda hoping its not a freshman and its a transfer.  That would be nice.  I am going to try REAL hard not to worry, and when I go there be open minded, friendly, and myself.  I guess I havent decided on cheerleading, maybe Im scared of failure?  Cuz I have to get a job for my car and to save, and then plus school work, and plus campus ministires, plus community service, plus I want to get involved in so much stuff, like clubs, intermurials and just be involved on campus.  I regret not doin that at fsc. I guess I have to just Trust in Him it will all work.  
So my last day is Friday at work, still have so much to get and errands but im really hoping I have some beach time and some time with friends.  
So this may seem a lil crazy.  But I want to write it.  I have read alot this summer.  The first book was about purity, and so was the 2nd.  I also bought a modesty book, and now im reading captiviating, and I kissed dating goodbye.  I kissed dating good bye isnt about never dating again.  Its about entrusting your lovelife to God and that God has something better for you with a life of sincere love, true purity, and purposeful singleness.  So the author Joshua Harris reminded me of myself, someone who grew up, in relationships, and found happiness from the opposite sex, and even when it was a pure relationship it still wasnt right, because it was what was fulfilling his life, and his time, and his happiness, and the wrong reasons,~>SOOOO ME!  Singleness is a time for you to find the Lord, to grow in Him, become more like Him.  Its your time to find YOUR purpose, YOUR happiness, and when everything is going beautifully one day, OUR BEAUTIFUL KING will BOOOOOM send u a great mate...you just have to TRUST!  and me, I never did.  I ALWAYS HAD TO HAVE A BOYFRIEND.  Ive been asked out this summer, but I realized, this summer had to be for me and Him.  In the book a girl confesses a d ream she had.  When the man she was marrying was holding her hand at the atlar, 6 other girls came up and held his hand, and they were girls from his past that he has giving his heart to.  I dont want to give my heart to a million different guys.  That saying "Youll date a million guys" I dont want that.  God says ONE man, and even thou I have had then men of my past, starting now, I only want to have ONE, I will only give my heart to my future husband.  So as Joshua Harris said it, he didnt date till he was ready for marriage.  Girls today put so much pressure to have a boyfriend, or  be married.  But as crazy as this sounds...I heard so many ppl who didnt kiss till marriage, and well I have been thinking about it.  In one book it says to put a line at how far u would go, and I said kissing, and it said okay, now try to go one above and set that as ur goal.  Well I know many ppl would say that its nuts, and u need to kiss, but im starting to think, if you could find a guy who truley loved you, and the Lord, they would do it, I mean its not for me, and for the Lord, and I mean relationships fail because of sexual things, and even thou kissing isnt bad, I know some christian spend so much time kissing that there is no realtionship.  I know its possible.  I know their are guys who would do it.  Might b a long wait.  But I trust Him.  Not saying I def feel this way, but if I date someone might be something to consider.  I mean how amazing would it be to have the first kiss at the alter when u say I do, u may kiss the bride!  And U know u would have an amazing relationship that was bulid off of friendship.  My book has u write about ur future husband, it says to wait, and I will because I know its worth the wait, and i never looked at it this way, but if u start praying for ur future husband and thinking of how u want him to be, u will fall in love with him, and ever time ur tested or tempted u can think about how much u truley love him and u will wait for him.  Save everything 4 him.  So many girls think their boyfriend is it and love them so much, but then they are heartbroken later cuz they gave themself away, and then when they do get married it hurts they didnt save it for the special one.  I will not let that happen.
I bought a real journal, and one goes with my purity book for prayers n such and the other one im going to start writing in it so i dont  always have to write it in here.  I dont really like the fact this is online-but i just love to write.  Ive always liked to write.  I love poetry.  Im kinda a deep person.  Everyone always looked at me as the ditzy peppy cheerleader.  Guys kind of just looked at me as the cute lil jamie but i dont think ne of them really ever tried to get to kno me. I use to see on tv how girls were hurt and couldnt trust again, and well I always said Im not ready 2 date again, but would anyways, and well now, i am really scared.  I know God has someone so amazing and I just have to trust Him, but I am having such a hard time trusting Guys.  Like I have been hurt so many times, and lied to so many times, and I just feel like I have lost all trust.  I dont want to be like that thou.  I really dont. But everytime I trust too easily, and then I get lied to, I trust, I get lied to again, its a cycle. I know Im about to enter a college where alot of guys are in Love w the Lord and arent like that, but im still scared, like how do i know.  I really have to trust the Lord with this.  Even as friends im scared =(  Well I just have to let Him take care of it, and I know hes got some nice surpises in store =)  

Wait for a man who calls you beautiful instead of hot, who has the patience when you're just having one of those days, who will sit beneath the dark sky and ask the Lord to show him if you're 'the one', or will hold you in his arms whether you're sad or just for no reason. Wait for the man who kisses you in the center of your forehead, who wants to show you off to the world when you're not feeling pretty, who holds your hand in front of your dad, one who is constantly reminding you of how much you make him a better person, loves being with you, and how he's the luckiest man in the world to have you. Oh yeah, and when he's with his friends, he says, 'that's her.'" --If he doesn't have all these things, pray hard about it. But if he does, still pray about it, but never pass up a chance to encourage him in the Lord even if he's not "the one". God will bring him to you in His timing Trust in Him.

So Im really trying to work on TRUSTING HIM, as well as buliding a stronger relationship.  I mean I have come SO far, but I really got to work on just dwelling in his presence every second and remembering its 4 Him not me!

So Brittany told me she is gettin engaged be4 fall break! Married in 2006! Ohhh Boy Congrats sweetie I am so glad God has matched u two so perfectly =) I cant waittttttt for the wedding and to see u oh so beautiful...as always! and be patient for that nite ; ) ; )

Lately I have been going to work, and spending time w my family, I havent seen many friends so I hope I do soon!!! I cant wait to get to school and get my life on track, I just feel like I do not really know what my dislikes/likes are, what I enjoy to do?  Well maybe I should do cheerleading.  Ive always loved that.  But I want to use my talents for the Lord but Im not sure what?  Maybe I should start writing poetry again.  Or taking photos.  I have to start doing things for myself too.  As well as others.  My poetry has always been about feelings, with guys, but im thinking of how beautiful it would be to write for my Jesus.  I need to stop worrying and just let it all work out.  Goodnight all..I love u ; )

What an A M A Z I N G summer it has been.  To think when it started all I could do was thinking about going to FL.  How much I hated it here.  And wanted to leave.  Now I am VERY excited but I kinda don't want to leave.  Me and my mother have came SO close, we have always been extrelmly close but now its like WHOA! I remember last year in FT Laud when the song In my daughters eyes came on and I almost cried I called my mom to tell her I missed her, and Jamie, Lauren, and Heather were all like I hate my mom!  Everyone thinks im crazy cuz me n my mom tell eachother everything.  There is nothing im ashamed to tell her, shes like my best friend.  Now that I have the Lord in my life, its been even better.  The relationship we both have with him has broughten us closer! We get ice cream together everynight, have gone out to dinner, shopping, and most importantly, AMERICAN IDOL!!!!! A M A Z I N G night I might say!
I was baptized on July 12th!! O my gosh what an expierence.  It was during tent meeting and they let us join in on the worship it was so beautiful.  Just being dropped in to the water in His name and being freed of my past and knowing Im not the same person, but most importanly...that night, the angels were dancing cuz so many people, young, my age, and old, had glorfied Him =)

When I think about the Lord
How He saved me, how He raised me
How He filled me w/ the Holy Ghost
How he healed me to the uttermost
When I think about the Lord
How he picked me up
Turned me around
How he set my feet
On solid ground
It makes me want to shout...
Hallelujah, thank you, Jesus
Lord, You're worthy
Of all the glory, and all the honor
And all the praise!!!

That song says it all! When I think about the Lord Im just sooo happy! He really changed me.  A few months ago I was sitting in my dorm room, stressed, and unhappy, and WHY, becuz I didnt know My Jesus!!! I was NOT doing things I am proud of.  But...because God loves us so much..he sent Jesus to save us! How amazing? The stupid lil things we do, HE DID FOR, he SUFFERED FOR...how can we NOT do our part and live for God! I think people think life is here and now..its not..its in eternity with Him..and eternity ALOT longer then here I might add!!
I just read a gift wrapped by God, and the bride wore white...WOW..what helpful books!!It helps girls keep that gift for their future husbands.  It also helps girl who have givin it up, realize that they can become pure again.  Jesus died for that, he forgives u!!!! One book talked about not kissing till ur wedding night, I donno if I could do that, but then again after reading this book its changed my perspective on so much.  First of all..I just bought a modesty book, I went shopping, no more mini skirts and low cut shirts for meeeee! I am HIS princess and Im going to dress like it =)  It talks about how God has made guys the way to desire us, and if we dress SEXY then we LOOK sexy, and as a Christian girl its our job to help our brothers in Christ and not dress like that! wow I never thought of that before!  Plus who wants to be with a guy who is with u for the way u look! This book made me realize singleness is such a gift.  This summer being single has giving me a chance to grow so much closer to Him, to make a real relationship.  Im listening to new music, dressing differently, even reading! But thats not even it, I realized EVERYTHING I do is for HIM, each day I try to dwell in his presence each second, yes its hard, but thats what its about, my relationship with Him.  I also realized there is no reason to settle, to just date anyone, I begun praying for my future husband, that God helps him face his challenges and stay pure.  I also wrote a vision statement of the women I wanna b on my wedding night.  This book really helps.  And as much as I regret the things I have done in my past, I know thats in my past, and Jesus forgive me, and any man who loves me will too.  I know my wedding night is going to be perfect.  Any guy can say hes a Christian, BUT dont settle for just a christian, wait for the one who has a relationship with Christ, and can challenge u and hold u accountable.  Someone who will pray with you, and love God first then you second.  The relationship wont hold together without the three.  
Okay so I am thinking about getting a job at a hotel, I will have enough time.  But then I think I kind of want to cheer. Do you ever have so much on ur mind but you just push it away so you can be happy?  Well my issue is a complain but never do nething about ne of it.  So I decide to forget and not worry.  But really I still worry and it never goes away and I continue to complain.  I have not written in here for awhile and I guess its because I realized anyone can read this.  Well I really want to get some stuff out.  I really love writing so this is where I came to.  People say that I complain too much.  Which is true.  I have tried to stop and improve because I am so blessed its incredible.  I have two amazing parents.  My mother is my best friend.  We have the best relationship, I can tell her anything.  I have a father who loves me so much and is such as passionate loving figure.  I have two lifes, one in the north one in the sunny FL.  So I am trying really hard to realize what I have and not complain.  Also people here don't all think highly of me.  I guess I still have some maturing to do.  I remember in high school when people would say they walked by me and I did not say high or I gave them a dirty look.  Which was not me trying to be rude.  It was cuz I did not see them.  I do that here too.  I need to be more observent.  Also sometimes Im a lil shy and when I do not become miss friendly when I meet someone they think im snobby when its actually me being shy.  I need to change this.  In high school I was not the kindest person.  I mean I had people who thought I was a snob but usually people who got to know me thought I was a sweetheart.  But I feel like here people just judge me. I guess its my fault.  I say things I should not say and do not always mean.  I am working on this too.  I want to be a better person.  Someone who does not judge and say mean things.  What else am I working on? Well I stopped drinking, right? I gave in...Lately I have not been drinking again.  I try not to say I never will again becuz if I do its a lie.  But I figure I can have a drink here n there, but I have no desire to get drunk.  I pray that I can stay strong and feel this way for a long time.  Im done hooking up with random boys.  I feel like I have lost who I want to be.  Everyone says in college u find urself.  I always grew up as the ditzy, little, snobby,cheerleader.  I had so many friends and was always having fun.  When I left I was in search of something greater.  I found it, I found myslef, I was so happy.  But I lost it.  I know what I want, now I just have to stay true to myself.  I dont care what anyone thinks.  I have grown up and matured but obviously I still have more to learn.  I try hard to be strong but everyday people here make me feel crappy.  They tell me im a bitch or a snob.  They tell me I could not go to a christian school, like they know school, or know what I want or am looking for.  I got into Calvin.  I want so bad to go, it seems like an amazing school, I think I could be myself there.  I do not care to go party go out n get drunk.  People here may read this and think im full of it but i dont care.  I am satisfied with watching movies and having girl nights and having a steady boyfriend.  I may seem like I have changed my mind but I have not.  I was lost, and this is what I want.  I also am looking at PBA i got in.  So we will see.  Part of me wants to stay here.  I just am so unsure.  I guess its worth it to start over. But there are people I do not want to leave =(  I guess I have to put it in Gods hands.  I have to stop worrying about what others say and follow my heart.  Theres another area where I have to follow my heart and not listen to others.....I guess sometimes I am not fully trufully with people here becuz I do not know what they will think.  But you kno what screw it.  I dont care.  There is a boy that I LOVE TALKING TO and I DONT CARE IF HES MILES AWAY! I believe that God puts certant people in ur life for reasons.  I also believe that its better to make it work with someone who you want to be with even if its hard rather than date someone just cuz its easy.  I told myself never to settle.  And I wont.  If I find what I want I wont let them get away.  We are spending spring break together so we will see from there.  You know what if you do not understand, I DONT CARE. Its my life not urs. Home...yeahhhhh, I could not WAIT to come home...but why am I not so happy?  Last night me and Katie went shopping and It was great to see her but I was so tired I came in and went to bed around 10.  I had to work 10-7 today and then when I was there they asked me to stay till 8.  Next week I have 45 hours.  Im excited I need the money.  But its like now I cannot go out as much.  But I guess this is growing up.  I want to go to Boston with my girls.  I want to go sledding..it better snow!  I want to go ice skating! I want to do fun things while I am home.  Not just sit in and be boring.  Lol.  So yeah I really hope it snows...it hasnt yet! =*(  I really do miss my girls back to fsc.  I really never noticed how close we had all gotten.  I have wanted to transfer for awhile now, but we are all so close, but you know they are transfering too...but then again I need to be strong.  I am transfering for the reason of wanting to be surrounding by a more Christian atmosphere.  But then again there are things at my school that I could be involved with.  It will be so hard to leave my friends behind at FSC...but then again maybe its better?  I need to do the right thing.  Home has been kinda sad, my brother and mom fight constanly.  Im reminded of how screwed up my brother is and how much he hurts my mom.  I noticed WHY I left this place.  Yeah I love my friends here..I love my family, but I know now why I left.  I left because I was unhappy, don't get me wrong I use to have sooo much fun...but when I went away I believe I did alot of growing up and maturing and I changed.  The things that were important to me are now superficial.  I realized I left to meet new people, to be on my own, to get away from my family problems.  Well when I went away I got the best gift anyone could ask for, I found God.  And everything after that moment in my life changed.  Now its weird, because I am lonely at times, wishing I had somebody.  But there are guys who have asked me out, but I know what I am looking for now and I do not want to just settle.  Sometimes I feel like Im wasting my time, and everything that I have done has been a waste. Maybe I should just go back to how I was.  But then I remember why I am doing this, and It brings a smile to my face.  I want a guy who is a Christan, who has morals, and respects me, and can care to know me.  I know back home I have never found anyone like that.  Once again another reason I left.  To get away from my old life and old me and the boys who only want to get some.  I know boys are like that in FL too but it has been amazing for me starting over.  I really wish I had someone to talk to.  But for now the only one who I feel like explaining this to, is my journal.  I need to do some thinking.  I need to decicde if I want to transfer or stay at FSC.  I need to decide what I want.  I hope this vacation turns around soon.  
Much <3

Jamie

As I sit in my dorm room I realize how FAST my life has gone, and how thankful I am for everything that I have.  Its amazing how fast we grow up.  I realize I get to have two sets of amazing friends and two homes.  I get the warm and the cold.  I get the beaches and the snow.  I am blessed with an amazing family.  I feel like yesterday I was starting Elm St with Katie..we were so nervous wed get lost! haha! Or then going to High school, the football games, the drama of HS, prom, graduation..all of it has such sentiment to me.  Ill never forget those amazing times.  Everyone says in college you find your true self and its funny because I have.  I have changed so much.  Its funny because before I came here me and stephaine both said wed probally go home not drinking and changed, and well its true.  Its funny how things happen, but like I always say, Everything happens for a reason.  But I thought coming here was going to be different than it is.  Growing up I have always had tons of friends.  I guess when I was younger I always had the repuation of the ditzy, snobby, cheerleader.  But when people got to know me, they got to know I wasnt like that, theres more to me.  I mean back in freshman year when people told Aaron not to bother because I wouldnt date him.  It bothers me when people are like that. But that was a long time ago.  But I think Aaron helped me be less superficial.  But I truley feel that college has changed me alot, I feel as if I have looked past the silly things that use to be important to me.  Drinking every night, guys, and partying.  Everytime something bad happened id always say no more drinking but hey I didnt care I did it again.  Even after the night with cote and them.  But now I just look at things so differently.  Not to sound stupid, but I am proud of myself.  Im not longer interested in just hangout with people because of there status, and Im not longer superficial w boys.  I dont feel like I need to explain myself to others.  I am just happy!  I use to think to be happy I needed to be dating someone.  I was happy with Aaron but after that I was hurt too much.  I realized I needed to be single and maybe id find someone here at college. Well that was wrong.  I no longer will settle.  I know what I want and I know hes worth the wait.  If I wanted so badly to be with the wrong ones just imagine how amazing it will be when I find him.  I think its better to be a little lonenly now and then and wait then to be with all the wrong ones.  So Ill wait ; )  
Its funny how things happen, and how after meeting someone here has changed me.  I guess God put him in life for a reason.  I use to think it was for us to be together.  But then I realized it was God wanting me to change my life.  And he helped me.  Ive never thought of myself the way I am now. But im happy.   
Its funny how I couldnt wait to go to college to change...because sometimes back home people didnt believe one thing about me.  And I guess its my fault, they way i acted.  But here alot of people didnt believe the truth either, but some are finally realizing the real me.  I hope back home maybe people will start to believe me.  
Anyways..I am thinking of transfering.  I love the weather and Im comfortable here.. but I know its not the best for me.  I hate when people here tell me that its the same everywhere because they do not know what I am looking for.  They do not know me.  They do not know.  I am annoyed at the fact people act like someone they are not. They lie just to fit in and are two faced.  I cant stand when someone always has to be right and have everything there way or they pull a hissy. I cant take it.  I try to stay away from fights and just get through this year.  I mean they are other people here that I love and its not like that.  But what I want is to be at a christian school.  Im looking to Calvin, Olivet, Cederville, PCC, PBA.  I know that there I can surround myself by others who want the same as myself.  I think id be alot happier.  
Well things here are not so bad, but school work is tough!  I miss everyone so much but its only 2 more days! Its going to be a blast to go to the Turkey bowl and to the Holiday Stroll =) Give me a call if you want to see me because Im not working again until Christmas.  

Alright..I need to go study...I <3 u ALl!!!

God Bless!!!!!

<3  Jamie
